window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Magic exists... and it doesn't want her. Her fated mate plans to change that.</b></p> <p>Lainie Eaves has no idea she's descended from shifters. She doesn't even know shifters exist because when she was born human, her grandparents made sure she would never learn the truth about her family.</p> <p>But now they're dead. And she's back in Hideaway Cove to deal with their crumbling old estate—and discover everything that was kept hidden from her.</p> <p>Hideaway Cove is the only safe haven griffin shifter Harrison Galway has ever known—a place where, as a shifter, he can live without hiding what he is. When gorgeous, curvy Lainie arrives in town, he knows at once that she's his fated mate.</p> <p>But her history with Hideaway Cove means where he sees a sanctuary, she only sees rejection. Can he heal her heart when all she wants to do is run away again?</p> <p>The Griffin's Mate <i>is a fated mates shifter romance where he falls first, with a cinnamon roll hero and a heroine who doesn't believe in magic or love—and is about to discover how wrong she is about both.</i></p> <p><i>Escape to Hideaway Cove, a small town with a magical secret. Each book in the Hideaway Cove series can be enjoyed as a standalone and features powerful shifters falling head over heels for their fated mates. No cliffhangers, and a guaranteed happy-ever-after in every book!</i></p>"; 
